Nautilus Middle School wrapped up their End of Year Awards Ceremonies June 5, 2019. Students were celebrated and recognized for their amazing achievements throughout the year! Special awards, Academic, American Citizenship, Athletic, Music, Science, & STEAM Awards were presented to many deserving students. NMS Band played for parents before and at intermission.
Thank you, Board Member Dr. Martin Karp of MDCPS for your participation and support.
Thank you to all parents and families attending to celebrate and support our NMS Students for their remarkable, admirable achievements. #GOSHARKS!

Dream in Green's End of Year Awards recognized schools and student achievements in environmental STEAM activities.
Nautilus Middle School won 1st Place. Tomas Dominguez, Pres. of Science STEAM Club attended and received awards for Nautilus Middle School.
Mr. Rene Bellmas won the Award for Inspirating Administrator Award.
Chase Brown, 7th grade, won Game Changer Award.
Dr. Gwen Foote won an Award for Innovation in Education. Congratualtions to our students, school, and community.
Thank you to Dream in Green for a brilliant program of environmental awareness through education.

Nautilus Middle School golf team named runner-up in county tournament in Miami-Dade County‚Äôs Golf Championship after defeating 12 local golf teams. BY ADRIANNE RICHARDSON - MIAMI HERALD

City of Miami Beach awarded our Nautilus Middle School Students with Certificates for TOP achievements in Regional Awards in South Florida Regional STEAM Competitions. Nautilus Middle School had 80 students participating in South Florida Regional Science & Engineering Fair and SECME Olympiad at 2019 STEAM EXPO at Miami Dade College and had more projects competing in this event than most schools in the MDCPS District. Drama Competitions were won on the State Level in Orlando, and these students were also recognized.
The City of Miami Beach awarded EVERY Student an award for Outstanding Achievements and a Proclamation to Dr. Gwendolyn Foote for her Outstanding Achievements in Science Education.

post_text: Nautilus Middle School 7th Grade Science students participated in Fairchild Challenge Million Orchid Project with Fairchild's STEM Mobile Lab on Nov 1. They will be working with this in-class project, working with cloning and cultivating native orchids for reintroduction into our neighborhood area later in the year. Follow up STEM Mobile Lab program will take place Feb 28.

post_text: Congratulations to Theatre Troupe 89320 for their amazing performances and presentations at The Florida State Theatre Festival on February 6th in Longwood, FL. Receiving Excellent medals were Jaxon Pfrogner for his Set Design on MacBeth; Asya Lobanova and Melanie Lagos for improvisation. And a Superior Medal was brought home by Asya Lobanova for her Pantomime entitled Departures. Huge thanks to the Nautilus PTSA for providing grants for this amazing trip.
